OL,3,GNEWSCHundreds of jobs to go at BBC News
OL,4,Cin first stage of major cost-cutting
OL,5,Cdrive
OL,6,
OL,7,FThe BBC is set to announce hundreds of
OL,8,Fjob losses in its News division next
OL,9,Fweek, according to reports in The
OL,10,FFinancial Times.
OL,12,FThe redundancies in News are the first
OL,13,Fstage of a major cost-cutting drive
OL,14,Flaunched ahead of critical funding
OL,15,Ftalks with ministers.
OL,17,FNews will be the first part of the
OL,18,Fcorporation to reveal detailed
OL,19,Fredundancy plans, and insiders warn the
OL,20,Fimpact could be visible to audiences.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,153,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15202
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F152A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/4
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCHundreds of jobs to go at BBC News
OL,4,Cin first stage of major cost-cutting
OL,5,Cdrive
OL,6,
OL,7,FEvery department has been told to cut
OL,8,Fcosts by roughly 10 per cent, part of a
OL,9,Fwider programme expected to see the
OL,10,Fcorporation shed around 2,000 jobs and
OL,11,Fsave hundreds of millions of pounds as
OL,12,Flicence fee income tightens.
OL,14,FNews, which employs about a quarter of
OL,15,Fthe BBC's 20,000-plus staff across TV,
OL,16,Fradio, apps and online, is likely to be
OL,17,Fhit hardest because so much of its
OL,18,Fspending goes on people, leaving fewer
OL,19,Fsavings options beyond headcount.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,153,140,200,120,0,100
